# Git workflow

When finishing changes in this repo:

1. Commit with a clear message describing why.
2. Push to `origin main` — do not create new version tags unless the user asks.
3. The canonical CDN link uses `@main`; pushing to main is enough for courses to get updates.

Only skip push if the user explicitly says not to, or if there are no changes to commit.
